fields.value: Replication data for: Legislative Coalitions in Presidential Systems: The Case of Uruguay

authorAffiliation.value: Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey

dsDescriptionValue.value: Includes web-appendix with extend results, legislator ideal-point estimates, original roll-call data and code to replicate the analyses presented in the paper.

publicationCitation.value: Zucco, Cesar.  Spring 2013. "Legislative Coalitions in Presidential Systems: The Case of Uruguay" Latin American Politics and Society.

files.description: This file is the main data file for the analysis in the paper. An version of this file for R is included in the .zip file, but, for convenience, it is also provided here in subsettable format.
files.label: factiondataset.tab

dataFile.description: This file is the main data file for the analysis in the paper. An version of this file for R is included in the .zip file, but, for convenience, it is also provided here in subsettable format.

files.description: Includes basic information about each vote in the other four files, as well as an indicator as to whether each faction in the Senate was part of the cabinet at the time of the vote. Can be matched to the roll call data file by the roll call number.
files.label: rollcallmetadata.csv

dataFile.description: Includes basic information about each vote in the other four files, as well as an indicator as to whether each faction in the Senate was part of the cabinet at the time of the vote. Can be matched to the roll call data file by the roll call number.

files.description: This .zip file includes a number of data files for R, as well as the basic code to replicate the results in the paper. Simply place all files in the same folder, change the path in the .R file accordingly, and run the analysis.
files.label: RReplicationFiles.zip

dataFile.description: This .zip file includes a number of data files for R, as well as the basic code to replicate the results in the paper. Simply place all files in the same folder, change the path in the .R file accordingly, and run the analysis.

files.description: Includes all roll calls taken in the Senate in the given legislature. File includes legislator name, party, faction, the list to which the legislator belonged, whether the legislator was a "Titular" or "Suplente", the number of votes the legislator voter on, and the legislator's vote in each roll call.
files.label: uyrc1985-1990.csv
